  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI am sending the same payload to two different geth nodes one running 1.7.2 and other 1.7.0. The payload is \r\n```json\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"method\":\"eth_getLogs\",\"params\":[{\"fromBlock\":\"0x254A31\",\"toBlock\":\"0x254A6E\",\"topics\":[\"0xddf252ad1be2c89b69c2b068fc378daa952ba7f163c4a11628f55a4df523b3ef\",null,null],\"address\":\"0x583cbbb8a8443b38abcc0c956bece47340ea1367\"}]}\r\n```\r\n#### Actual behaviour and steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nVersion `1.7.2` The log is missing, I am testing on **ropsten infura** [https://ropsten.infura.io](https://ropsten.infura.io/)\r\nVersion `1.7.0` Running a private node, I can see the log as well as we can check from the log API of [ropsten etherscan](https://ropsten.etherscan.io) with the ENDPOINT \r\n\r\n`https://ropsten.etherscan.io/api?module=logs&action=getLogs\r\n&fromBlock=2443825\r\n&toBlock=2443886\r\n&address=0x583cbbb8a8443b38abcc0c956bece47340ea1367\r\n&topic0=0xddf252ad1be2c89b69c2b068fc378daa952ba7f163c4a11628f55a4df523b3ef`\r\n\r\nIs it happening due to difference in versions? But from my understanding the logs should be consistent. What can be the cause of log not being present on one node and one more observation I made is that i am able to see the transaction receipt.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.7.2` and `1.7.0`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n\r\n",
